The Amadeus Travel Python Sample Code provides installation, a getting started guide, initialization, and documentation. Developers can integrate flights, hotels, and locations data into applications.
The Amadeus Travel Ruby Sample Code demonstrates how to make an API call, registering for a developer account and setting up an application.
The Amadeus Self-Service PHP Sample Code demonstrates how to display results for flight low fare search and hotel search.
This Wazo Python Sample Code is an event handler implementation for Wazo chat databases. The snippet shows how to create and delete users, and sessions.
The Wazo User test Python Sample Code demonstrates several database models. This application shows how to create users by specifying an UUID, and add sessions.
This Wazo Python Sample Code implements several tenant database methods. The snippet demonstrates how to create, and delete tenants.
This Wazo Python Sample Code is an integration test for database session methods. The application shows how to retrieve sessions by UUID.
This Wazo Python Sample Code is a test database line implementation. The snippet demonstrates how to retrieve a line by ID, get devices, and implement error handling.
This Wazo JavaScript Sample Code is a test voicemail implementation. The snippet demonstrates several voicemail operations for a specific caller.
This Wazo JavaScript Sample Code demonstrates line parsing operations.
This Wazo JavaScript Sample Code is an implementation for call logging. The test application demonstrates how to parse a call log entry.
This Wazo JavaScript Sample Code demonstrates call methods. The snippet displays a call's elapsed time, and demonstrates call related boolean operations.
This Wazo JavaScript Sample Code demonstrates how to implement WebRTC Phone functionalities with applications. This supports authentication, music, and dialer modules.
This Sample Code serves as a template that integrates Wazo with React Native applications.
This Wazo JavaScript Sample Code demonstrates how to parse a plain session to domain, and access voicemails. This also shows how to retrieve numbers, and handle session expiration.
The OAuth.io JavaScript Sample Code demonstrates how to connect a user via Facebook via popup mode and redirection mode for authentication purposes.
The OAuth.io iOS Sample Code demonstrates how to use the SDK by configuring a provider on a dashboard. Developers will need a public key.
The OAuth.io Android Sample Code demonstrates how to implement authentication features into an application.
The OAuth.io Cordova Node.js Sample Code demonstrates how to integrate authentication features into PhoneGap applications.
The Sketchapp JavaScript Sample Code demonstrates how to interact indirectly with the API to access design features to build websites.
This Wazo Sample Code demonstrates how to create a new user profile, and how to parse a profile to domain.
This Wazo JavaScript Sample Code performs several contact tests that check for duplicates, and check for disconnected clients.

The Slack Easy Peasy Bot JavaScript Sample Code demonstrates how to build a simple bot to run on laptop and desktop computer. The bot will be connected to Slack and https://botkit.ai/ will be required to start.
The Slack Message Buttons Node.js Sample Code demonstrates how to implement buttons into a messaging application.

The Slack Bot Node.js Sample Code by Google demonstrates how to build a Slack bot with the BotKit toolkit. Developers will run the bot on the Google Cloud Platform, interacting with the bot in a live Slack channel.
The Slack Bot Ruby Sample Code demonstrates how to build a bot in Ruby language.
The Slack Bot Python Sample Code demonstrates how to build a bot in Python language.
The Slack Sentiment Analysis Python Sample Code demonstrates how to implement a sentiment analysis feature into a messaging application.
The Slack Web Curl Sample Code demonstrates how to authorize with a token to make calls. Developers will receive JSON responses in return.
The Slack Build a Bot Swift Sample Code demonstrates how to write a Slack bot and deploy in Heroku. The project is compatible with Linux in an editor of choice.
The SketchApp SVGO Curl Sample Code demonstrates how to compress SVG files after a developer exports from Sketch. In addition, it shows how to hook the ExportSlices action.
The SketchApp Hello World Curl Sample Code demonstrates how to add a menu command to the Plugins, processing an action when a developer selects the code.
The Tink JavaScript Sample Code demonstrates how to integrate the Tink API to fetch users' account and transaction data.
The Tink iOS Sample Code demonstrates how to integrate apps with the Tink API. Xcode project, example server, and example app available.
This Bitex.la JavaScript Sample Code shows how to implement trading bots. The snippet demonstrates how to create buying bots, and selling bots. Additionally, this shows how to cancel operations.
This Bitex.la JavaScript Sample Code is a test order book implementation. Ask, bid, buy, and sell methods are demonstrated.
This Bitex.la JavaScript Sample Code demonstrates how to get payments, create an asynchronous POS implementation, and create a payment.
This Bitex.la JavaScript Sample Code demonstrates how to get market data. This retrieves tickers, transactions, and order books.
The Tink Access User Data Curl Sample Code demonstrates how to make requests to obtain access to user data.
The Tink Tokens Curl Sample Code demonstrates how to exchange access tokens to authorize the API.
The Electron JavaScript Sample Code demonstrates how to use the framework to build apps with JavaScript, HTML, and CSS based on Node.js and Chromium.
The Kintone Java Sample Code demonstrates how to use the SDK by setting a domain, the application id, a login name, and the password.
The Ionic Framework iOS Sample Code provides a setup to build an iOS app on macOS.
The Ionic Framework Android Sample Code provides a setup to build an Android app on Windows, macOS, and Linux.
The Flutter Google Maps iOS Sample Code demonstrates how to integrate Google Maps into iOS applications.
This Bitex.la JavaScript Sample Code demonstrates several funding operations. The application shows how to implement Bitcoin deposits and wallet withdrawals.
The Flutter Google Maps Android Sample Code demonstrates how to integrate Google Maps into Android applications.
The Flutter Age Calculator iOS Sample Code demonstrates how to integrate an age calculator feature into an iOS application.
This Bitex.la JavaScript Sample Code implements API Key methods. The application demonstrates asynchronous methods for creating and revoking an API Key.
The Flutter Age Calculator Android Sample Code demonstrates how to integrate an age calculator feature into an Android application.
The Flutter Frenzy Chat iOS Sample Code demonstrates how to implement a chat into an iOS application.
The Flutter Frenzy Chat Android Sample Code demonstrates how to implement a chat into Android application.
The Twitch Swift Sample Code by Christopher Perkins demonstrates how to access the Helix API to integrate game analytics, leaderboard, clips, games, streams, users, extensions, and videos.

This Cidaas Sample Code is a Xamarin Android template application that integrates basic core functionalities with Android applications. This test application supports login operations, and offers a simple user interface. Android 5.0+ is required.
This Cidaas Sample Code demonstrates how to integrate the OAuth 2.0 interceptor module with Java applications.
The SingStat Retrieve Metadata Python Sample Code demonstrates how to make a request to receive metadata in JSON format as a response.
The SingStat Retrieve Metadata JavaScript Sample Code demonstrates how to make a GET request with JSON data type to receive metadata as a response.
The SingStat SearchID Python Sample Code demonstrates how to import a JSON format to make a request to the table builder endpoint.
The SingStat SearchID JavaScript Sample Code demonstrates how to search a resource ID with the table builder URL.

This Cidaas Cordova Sample Code demonstrates how to set-up and manage authentication and authorization in Cidaas enabled applications. Included are snippets for retrieving user profiles, validating Tokens, and renewing Tokens.
The AffiniPay Quick Bill Curl Sample Code demonstrates how to access the contacts endpoint with token authorization.
The AffiniPay Payment Gateway Curl Sample Code demonstrates how to authenticate an endpoint with a key. The example shows www.chargeio.com.
The AffiniPay Authentication Curl Sample Code demonstrates how to generate an authentication code to access payments scope.

The AffiniPay Merchant Application Curl Sample Code demonstrates how to validate a test with merchant information, business address, federal TAX ID, owner's details, operating account name, account bank name, and account routing number.

This Nexus Mods NodeJS Sample Code demonstrates API sample requests and the expected output for file, games and more. Nexus provides community driven websites and a platform for a modding site and communities to upload work for others to download and use in their games.
This Tanker Ruby Sample Code can be used as a template to build server integrations. The application demonstrates how to use Tokens to authenticate users.
The Flutter Pokemon iOS Sample Code demonstrates how to create a Pokemon application in an iOS device.
The Flutter Pokemon Android Sample Code demonstrates how to build a Pokemon application for Android.
The Flutter Beautiful Wallpaper iOS Sample Code demonstrates how to use Firebase tools to build a wallpaper app on iOS.
The Flutter Instagram Clone iOS Sample Code demonstrates how to create a user interface for Instagram to use on an iOS device.
The Flutter Instagram Clone Android Sample Code demonstrates how to build an Instagram user interface clone on an Android app.
The Flutter WhatsApp Clone iOS Sample Code demonstrates how to build the clone interface of a WhatsApp application for iOS devices.
The Flutter WhatsApp Clone Android Sample Code demonstrates how to build a WhatsApp clone in Flutter.
The Foursquare Mr. Jitters Android Sample Code demonstrates how to find coffee places by parsing responses from the Foursquare API on Android.
The Foursquare Augmented Reality Unity Sample Code demonstrates how to build an Augmented Reality App using the Foursquare API + Mapbox + ARKit.
The Goodreads Curl Sample Code demonstrates how to use the API by using methods replacing with an API Key.
The Klarna Payments JavaScript Sample Code demonstrates how to initialize the SDK with an option to use a client token to create a session.

The Klarna REST Core .NET Sample Code demonstrates how to access the API in REST architecture. Additional examples at https://github.com/klarna/kco_rest_dotnet/tree/v3.0/Klarna.Rest/Klarna.Rest.Core.Examples
The Klarna Payments .NET Sample Code demonstrates how to integrate a payment session with purchase country, currency, order amount, order tax amount, and order line.
The Klarna Order Management .NET Sample Code demonstrates how to acknowledge an order capture an order, and cancel an order.
The Klarna PHP Sample Code demonstrates how to install the SDK with composer autoloader.
The Klarna Hosted Payments Java Sample Code demonstrates how to include merchant URL, privacy policy, and payment method category.
The Klarna Settlement Card Java Sample Code demonstrates how to run code by accessing a client username, password, and HTTP transport.
The Klarna Payments Card Java Sample Code provides payments resource examples that include credit session, order, and customer token generation.
The Klarna Merchant Card Java Sample Code demonstrates how to run an example code to access merchant card information.
The Klarna Checkout Java Sample Code demonstrates how to fetch a checkout order, create, and update a checkout order.
The Close.io Python Sample Code demonstrates how to post a lead, get 5 most recently updated opportunities, and fetch multiple leads with syntax.
The Close.io Python Sample Code demonstrates how to make a request with an API Key. API base URL available.
The Klipfolio REST Connector Curl Sample Code demonstrates how to create a data source using a REST and URL connectors that link to any service.

The Klipfolio Data Source Curl Sample Code demonstrates how to create a new data source from Facebook. Developers can authenticate with OAuth token to make calls that retrieve responses in JSON formats.
The TransUnion JavaScript Sample Code demonstrates how to add the TransUnion digital verification feature into a website. It allows gathering a customer activity on a site.
